At times, customers see the banner on the Administration page:

{noformat}
System Administrator made configuration changes in section 'Plugins' at 11/Nov/2014 03:04. It is recommended that you perform a re-index. For more information please see the JIRA Documentation.
{noformat}

And the reason behind this is we ran an update to the plugin and JIRA will issue the banner when there are changes on the plugin's end.

Reindexing could be resource intensive if the instance is large. Having the banner there, the administrators are recommended to run indexing manually where they would need to plan and perform during off peak hours. This brings extra overhead to our customers.

*Suggestions*

* Do not display the banner if the plugin change is not crucial and does not really require an indexing.
* To trigger automated background reindex during a release, thus customers can come in the next morning without seeing the message.

